{"id": "EUVD-2022-55412", "enisaUuid": "3ff6204b-48cc-33ef-bfcf-1a8f321936f8", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nPCI: dwc: Deallocate EPC memory on dw_pcie_ep_init() errors\n\nIf dw_pcie_ep_init() fails to perform any action after the EPC memory is\ninitialized and the MSI memory region is allocated, the latter parts won't\nbe undone thus causing a memory leak.  Add a cleanup-on-error path to fix\nthese leaks.\n\n[bhelgaas: commit log]", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:51", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-17T21:31:18", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e7599a5974d4c64eaae8009c3f2e47b9e3223e07", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b03a8f1264ea8c363bec9ef6e37b467f27cb04ea", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2d546db5c80c45cac3ccd929550244fd58f4ff58", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3b453f5d06d1f1d6b20a75ea51dc7b53ae78f479", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8161e9626b50892eaedbd8070ecb1586ecedb109", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50146"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50146"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0c085777-6460-3ded-bcce-b98a171f6a33", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.61"}, {"id": "1ca6ccf6-4c29-33d6-918f-d6ea64fb67de", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "32bb7752-62a3-3bd6-b796-649a0b3c972e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.137"}, {"id": "4a6ba1fa-137a-39e1-ad5c-2b992f9ef407", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2fd0c9d966cc11bb5f73556dd788d12f501d8755 <e7599a5974d4c64eaae8009c3f2e47b9e3223e07"}, {"id": "63dd9cdd-435a-3a63-a51b-9f2688feb1cc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2fd0c9d966cc11bb5f73556dd788d12f501d8755 <8161e9626b50892eaedbd8070ecb1586ecedb109"}, {"id": "6cc1aa59-c124-38e6-b00b-265e68664b75", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2fd0c9d966cc11bb5f73556dd788d12f501d8755 <2d546db5c80c45cac3ccd929550244fd